4. THE FRANCISCAN SCHOOL, faithful to the spirit of its founder, is marked by a preference for affective spirituality, love of the Cross, and absolute poverty. For a more detailed bibliography of the Franciscan School 'see V. Mills, 0. F. M., Bibliography of Franciscan' Ascetical Writers vo. Fran- ciscan Educational Conference, Washington, 1926, pp. 248-332.

