perfect as also your heavenly Father is perfect. " z There- fore, the Eternal Father proposes Him to us as pur model. At His baptism and His transfiguration He said: "This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased." 2 Because He is well pleased in Him, the Eternal Father wills that we imitate His only-begotten Son. Thus with perfect assurance bur Lord tells us : " I am the way... no man cometh to the Father but by me.. .-learn of me because I am meek and humble of .heart... . I have given you an example that as I have done to you so you do also. " 3 At bottom the Gospel is ,no more than a relation of the deeds and traits .of our Lord's sacred person - proposed to us as a model for our imitation : "Jesus began, to do and to teach." 4 Christianity in turn is nothing more than the imitation of Cririst. St. Paul gave this as the sum- total of all our duties : " Be ye followers of me as I also am of Christ. " S

