     2) This is what makes all Christians brothers. From now on there is neither Jew nor Greek, neither free- man nor slave; we are all one in Christ Jesus. 2 We are all in closest fellowship so that what is profitable" unto one is profitable unto all others. "No matter how great the variety of gifts, or how great the diversity of offices, the whole body derives gain from whatever good there is in each member, and each member in turn shares in the common good of the body. This doctrine reveals to us the reasons why our Lord could say that whatever we do to the least of His little ones we do unto Him ; 3 for the head is one with the members.

