763. 

     1) We must secure our perseverance in good, and mortification offers without doubt one of the best means we ' have to keep free from sin.' What causes us to surrender to temptation is the love of pleasure or the horror of hard- ship, the hardship of the struggle. Mortification combats this twofold tendency, which is really but one;-for by having

