fact this; Saints ^pfalk ages, those ; that have been beatified; in these latter days vas 'well' . : as those "of old, have .severely chastised their bodies and their exterior senses, .well aware that man's whole. Being must :ipe brought : into subjection, that -in the. state of fallen nature, man's whole being^ must be crucified if he is to belong wholly to God. We shall therefore examine in- succession the entire range of morti- fications beginning with those that are exterior in character, finally arriving at those .of a more interior nature. This is the logical order; in actual practice we must learn how to combine them, and make proper use of them.". ' '.

I. The* Mortification of the Body f and the Exterior Senses _. v , t ;

