The chief means of growing in this virtue is the prayer- ful consideration of these examples and the ardent petition to Our Savior to make us share in His prudence.

1034. 

      2) The constituent elements of this virtue must then be fostered, namely, common-sense, a habit of reflect- ion, readiness to consult others, determination, foresight and caution.

1035. 

      3) Lastly, efforts must be made to adorn pru- dence with those qualities of which St. James speaks. After distinguishing true from false wisdom he adds : " But

*Mn t XVI, 12. 2 Matth., VI, 33. 3 Matth., X, 16. ^ Mark, XIII, 33.

