1142. 

      2) During the course of His public life Jesus does not cease to practice this forgetfulness of self to the extent compatible with His mission. He is, no doubt, obliged. to proclaim both by word and deed that He is. the Son of God; yet, He does so in a discreet, measured way, .sufficiently clear to reach the minds of men of good will, but 'not with such evidence as- to force assent. His humil- 'ity appears in everything He does. /'. ,

