2 THE SPIRITUALITY OF ST. PAUL" ' -

/ By a different procedure St. Paul arrives at the same conclusions as the Synoptics. The central idea with him is not indeed the King- dom, but the saving plan of God Who desires to save and to sanctify all men, Jews and. Gentiles, through His Son, Jesus Christ, made the Head of the human race and into Whom we must all be incorporated :

., XXII, 40. 2 Matth., XXII, 36-40. sMatth., VI, 9. * Matth.,.Vll, 21. 5 Matth., VI, 26-33. 6 Matth., VII, 7-8. ' ' TMatth., XXIII, 8. -t-Matth., XXV, 40. 9 Matth., V, 44. - -:; ,?. >Matth., XI, 29. ,'-'; . .-j.i ,2 ;

